⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 96/120 – End-to-End ETL Pipeline Challenge

🎤 Interview Question

Build an ETL pipeline that performs the following:

1. Read employee data.


2. Validate records.


3. Remove duplicates (keep latest record).


4. Identify new and updated records.


5. Merge data into the target.


6. Perform reconciliation checks.




---

✅ Recommended Solution (Pipeline Flow)

Read Source
      ↓
Validate Data
      ↓
Remove Duplicates
      ↓
CDC (Insert / Update)
      ↓
MERGE into Target
      ↓
Reconciliation
      ↓
Success Report

Key PySpark Components

Read data → spark.read

Validation → filter()

Deduplication → row_number()

CDC → left_anti, join()

Merge → Delta Lake MERGE

Validation → count(), sum(), countDistinct()



